The Academic Staff Union of Universities has called on the police to fish out those, who killed Prof Gideon Okedayo. Okedayo, a senior lecturer at the Ondo State University of Science and Technology in Okitipupa, was found dead on Monday night. He was kidnapped on September 5, 2019 while traveling on Igara-Auchi to his hometown. SaharaReporters had reported how the body of the late academic was recovered from the bush.



